The Commission shall, by means of implementing acts, designate one or several entities to operate a system for 
assignment of UDIs pursuant to this Regulation (‘issuing entity’). That entity or those entities shall satisfy all of the 
following criteria: 
(a)  the entity is an organisation with legal personality; 
(b)  its system for the assignment of UDIs is adequate to identify a device throughout its distribution and use in 
accordance with the requirements of this Regulation; 
(c)  its system for the assignment of UDIs conforms to the relevant international standards; 
(d)  the entity gives access to its system for the assignment of UDIs to all interested users in accordance with a set of 
predetermined and transparent terms and conditions; 
(e)  the entity undertakes to do the following: 
(i)  operate its system for the assignment of UDIs for at least 10 years after its designation; 
(ii)  make available to the Commission and to the Member States, upon request, information concerning its system 
for the assignment of UDIs; 
